# Repute Project Rules

## Font Usage

- Always use Mona Sans as the primary font (font-main class)
- Use Geist Sans for secondary text (font-sans class)
- Use Geist Mono for code elements (font-mono class)

## Color System

- Use custom color variables: --myprimary, --mysecondary, --myaccent
- Apply colors with Tailwind classes: text-myaccent, bg-myprimary, etc.

## Component Guidelines

- Follow shadcn/ui component patterns
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Maintain consistent spacing and typography
- Ensure responsive design for all components

## Code Style

- Use TypeScript with strict typing
- Follow Next.js App Router conventions
- Use server components by default, client components only when needed
- Implement proper error handling and loading states

## File Structure & Organization

- Place components in `/components` directory
- Use `/lib` for utilities and shared functions
- Keep API routes in `/app/api` following RESTful patterns
- Use `/app` directory structure (page.tsx, layout.tsx, loading.tsx, error.tsx)
- Group related components in subdirectories (e.g., `/components/ui`, `/components/forms`)

## Performance & SEO

- Use Next.js Image component for all images with proper alt text
- Implement proper meta tags and Open Graph data
- Use dynamic imports for heavy components
- Optimize bundle size with tree shaking
- Implement proper loading states and error boundaries

## Accessibility (a11y)

- Use semantic HTML elements
- Add proper ARIA labels and roles
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
- Maintain proper color contrast ratios
- Test with screen readers
